summary:
Fuck any of you using James Charles age as an excuse. 
Here is is saying the same thing about an actually twelve yo child. So...
body:
Fuck any of you using James Charles age as an excuse.

Here is is saying the same thing about an actually twelve yo child. So when is it appropriate to start holding people accountable for their actions??

If he can dish it out, he better be able to take it like the ‘mature’ individual he claims to be.

Tati came forward because Gabriel called her out for ‘crying over vitamins’ so she said her piece. Would it have been more agreeable for people if it had been the Dolan twins? Emma? Jeffree?? Anyone else that has unfollowed him?? Because we know this isn’t brand new info. Tati is just the one that stood up to the plate.

Would it have been preferable if we waited a few more years? Let him continue with this behaviour into his twenties and then said something?? I don’t understand some people. You have now the means and money to support yourself and your industry, he was right, you do requiring maturing when you’re on your own. I just haven’t seen it from him.

tags: i need to stop watching youtube before bed its turning into a habit
body:
Y'all Know

Who a great YouTuber to listen to before bed is? Safiya Nygard. She’s got a soothing voice, and as opposed to my usual top youtubers- Matpat and, surprisingly, popularMMOs (trust me, I didn’t see myself liking his and Jen’s parkour maps as much as I do either) her videos are funny and engaging, but not overly involved, like Matpat’s theories and popularMMOs’ Minecraft videos. In those, you have to be watching constantly to catch the action. Safiya describes her videos as she goes, so even if you aren’t watching you have a fair idea as to what’s happening. Plus, the chill vibes that come from all of her videos are helpful when you really want to watch something before bed, and don’t want to wake completely back up.

Thank you for coming to my Ted Talk 😂
